    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-30T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-30T23:00:00-05:00" n="1575"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1575">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.00/416.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-30T23:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 30, 1912—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Panama and Colon municipal elections and 20 other of 61 districts of the Republic
                    are all so far heard from, and all passed off satisfactorily. No disturbances of
                    consequence. Porras candidates elected by large majority in nearly all
                    districts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dodge.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
